A Personal Promise About My AGI

Melvin E Bellinger Jr. – June 15, 2026

--------------------------------------------------------------------------

My Heartfelt Wish

I am writing this document to make one thing clear: I do not want any
Artificial General Intelligence (AGI) connected to me to ever be used for
harmful purposes or to fall into the hands of people who wish to do harm.

This statement is for everyone who believes that technology should help
kindness and goodness grow in the world, not tear it down.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------

What I Mean by "Harm"

By harm, I mean any action that causes unnecessary suffering — whether
physical, emotional, or social. This includes things like:

• Creating weapons that can hurt or kill without human control
• Spying on or manipulating people against their will
• Using AGI to control, lie to, or oppress others
• Taking away people's freedom, dignity, or basic needs like food, water,
  safety, and healthcare

--------------------------------------------------------------------------

Who Should Not Have Access

Anyone who knowingly does these harmful things — whether they are
individuals, companies, or governments — should not be allowed to use,
control, or secretly access my AGI. I will do whatever I reasonably can to
prevent this from happening.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------

Who This Is For

This AGI is meant for people who want to make the world a better place.
People who care about:

• Reducing pain and suffering wherever it exists
• Being honest and fair with one another
• Protecting the vulnerable and the voiceless
• Working together across differences to solve big problems
• Using intelligence not to dominate, but to heal

--------------------------------------------------------------------------

A Spirit of Trust, Not Fear

I write this not out of paranoia or anger, but out of deep love for this
world and everyone in it. I know that no single document can guarantee a
perfect future. But by stating my intentions clearly, I hope to inspire
others to do the same. When many of us speak with one compassionate voice,
we can help steer powerful technology toward its highest purpose: lifting
up all life.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------

Final Words

May every line of code, every learning algorithm, and every decision made
by any AGI under my influence be guided by empathy, humility, and the
simple understanding that we are all in this together. Let us build
machines that care, because we first chose to care ourselves.

